[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Gaussian splatting was everywhere at NAB this year. It was in award winners, there were new camera rigs, there was 4D capture, and there was even standalone VR demos that genuinely stopped me in my tracks. So, here\'s everything I saw last week. My first up was with Alex Henry and his team at Origins Spin who took my'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'portrait in 3D. And then a little bit later in the day, I went straight over to see Ren from Corridor Digital give a talk about splatting using the anti-gravity A1 drone. He actually gave me a little bit of a shout-out, too. Michael on the back can tell you all'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'more if you want to learn more about Gaussian splatting. You can go to the whole website on Radiance Fields. Yeah, the smoothness of it. I highly recommend it if you\'re interested in this stuff. I\'ll admit I am a bit biased here because I have been testing the A1 and Insta360 drone for splat capture just'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'makes so much more sense. Later that afternoon, I joined B&amp;H Photo, Volinga, and Xgrid for a panel on splatting in production. This was totally new to me to see examples of Shrinking and Rooster on Apple TV and HBO, which have both'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'been using Gaussian splatting. I mean, look how lifelike these examples are. These were captured by District Cinema and Digital Film Tree, which just look amazing. Xgrid also came in nominated for four best product awards with the Pearl Cam, and they won all four. They'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'won for intelligent technology, graphics editing and VFX, remote production, and also for camera. Sony was another big winner taking best in show from TVTech for Zen, which is their splat stack. And their splat offerings are going to get'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty robust. They now have an iOS capture for Sony mirrorless camera called Navi that basically guides coverage and actually mounts a phone directly into the mirrorless hot shoe. And then they have a cloud-based reconstruction pipeline called Spatial'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Scan, which should be launching later this year. They were also showing splats running on their glasses-free 3D spatial reality display. And then they also have an Unreal Engine plugin through Zen Spatial Renderer. They started to show some of the relighting and some of the other capabilities you can do in there.'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'However, Sony also was showing more on the camera rig side, too, from a company called Arcturus. I got to take a look at their actual rig, which is super portable, actually, and they\'re starting to get a ton of demand for dynamic Gaussian splatting. But that was not the only place that 4D or dynamic Gaussian'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'splats were popping up at NAB. In fact, they seem to be everywhere. I stopped at Emergent Vision who had a camera rig running reconstruction previews on the floor. And in the T-Mobile booth, Radiant Images showed their Meridian rig, which is actually a 4D GS rig built'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'entirely from iPhones. And they did win best product for remote production, too. Their lead engineer gave me a demo of the results. They\'ve been partnering with Gracia as well to show some of their reconstructions. And I\'ll say they\'re just looking amazing. Innotech'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'also was showing results from their 75-camera Red array running a couple of different demos, one of which was a band. They showed some martial artists, and they also showed this really cool multi-exposure experimental capture done with Satellite Labs, but the'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fidelity was looking awesome. Though the standout of the entire show for me was 4D VAI. It managed to pack 70 cameras in a pretty small footprint. They captured My name is Michael Rebholz. I am here at NAB 2026 and showcasing some of the'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'things with dynamic, otherwise known as 4D Gaussian splatting, which it creates very, very lifelike dynamic 3D video. And we can see here, you can go around, you can go pause, you can slow down, and speed up. Uh and yeah, we are just kind'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of showing what is now possible in the world of imaging, which is pretty ridiculous. We have access to very lifelike 3D. And then also gave me a whole bunch of demos running standalone on a Quest headset. And legitimately,'

[03:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the fidelity in VR was unreal. I kept trying to pet this virtual cat and was completely blown away by some of the things that they were showing. But Gaussian splatting also kept showing up. If you saw any of the Gaussian splatting'

[03:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'examples done at the Olympics this year, Z Cam was actually the camera that captured those, and their team was there, too. Lightcraft also demoed their production tool Spark, and District Cinema showed captures alongside Terra, their spatial media organizer. Chaos was'

[03:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'running really crispy splats in a live media setting using V-Ray, and they also announced relighting support, too, in V-Ray\'s latest update for Gaussian splatting. Also, AccuWeather announced Immersive Cast, a splat-powered weather system. And then I also did a second'

[03:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'panel, this time as a moderator with Volinga, RCS Studios, and Katherine Bilsbury. We spoke about where Gaussian splatting is making an impact on previs, techvis, and where it\'s beginning to show up as final pixels. That was everything I saw at NAB this year'

[04:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'related to Gaussian splatting, but I am curious to see if I missed anything or what you guys felt like was the most important or coolest thing from this list here. It\'s very obvious that media and entertainment is turning their attention directly to Gaussian'

[04:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'splatting, and I\'m really looking forward to what\'s coming next from this industry. Next week, I\'m headed to a geospatial and construction conference and will be providing an update there. But until then, this is the latest of industry updates using Gaussian splatting in the world today. And with'

[04:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that in mind, I will see everyone in the next one.'
